Since we are on the topic of &quot;Amerasian&quot;, although it's not the topic of this threat tha I originally reated.<br><br>
As a Vietnamese American I know this that of all the Amerasian kids, the Black Amerasian kids suffered the most.  It's a dark side of us human that one's worthy based on the color of the skin.  It's a shame, a sin! to judge other that way but it's very true.  After the war, many White Amerasians found a home to live with.  I am not so sure of so called &quot;home&quot; but a place to stay.  However, many of the Black Amerasian kids were living on the street as beggars.  As a result.......crimes.  <br><br>
When the U.S. government began to take Amerasian home back in the early 90, most Black Amerasian were left behind until the last trip.  What I just told you is not an observation but stories that many Black Amerasian told me.<br><br>
May God punish those who judged other by the color of their skin.  This's not to be political correctness but arose from A HUMAN CONSCIENCE.
